    <p class="section-number">08 — Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">BBQ grill repair — what SoCal homeowners ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does BBQ grill repair cost?</h3>
        <p>Diagnostic is $89, waived with repair. Standard portable grill repairs run $120–$320. Luxury built-in repairs run $250–$600+. Cleaning service $65–$150. Written estimate before any work begins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Which areas of Southern California do you cover for BBQ grill repair?</h3>
        <p>Same-day across <strong>Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties</strong> — Malibu, Bel Air, Beverly Hills, Pacific Palisades luxury outdoor kitchens; Newport Coast and Newport Beach OC outdoor kitchens; Westlake Village, Hidden Hills-adjacent, and Thousand Oaks; Temecula wine-country and IE estate outdoor kitchens. Eight service territories total. BHGS Licensed #A49573.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My BBQ smells like gas — what do I do first?</h3>
        <p>Turn off the grill and gas supply immediately. Call your gas utility — SoCalGas at 1-800-427-2200 across most of LA, OC, Ventura, and parts of SB; Southwest Gas at 1-877-860-6020 for Riverside, Anaheim, Long Beach, and parts of SB. They verify and clear the area at no charge. Then call us at {phone} for the repair. Gas utility first, appliance repair second.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My burners won't ignite — what should I check first?</h3>
        <p>Remove the grill grates and heat plates and clean the burner ports with a wire brush. Grease-clogged ports are the most common cause of ignition failure in SoCal's year-round grilling environment. If the ports are clean and there's no spark, that's an igniter. If there's a spark but no flame, that's a gas valve or regulator issue.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair Lynx, Alfresco, and Fire Magic built-in BBQ grills?</h3>
        <p>Yes. These are the luxury built-in brands we service most across SoCal — Malibu, Bel Air, Beverly Hills, Pacific Palisades, Newport Coast, Newport Beach, Westlake Village, and Temecula wine-country estates. Parts may need to be ordered — we quote parts cost before ordering. Repair almost always makes financial sense on these grills given their replacement cost.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can you service my outdoor kitchen refrigerator and side burner at the same time?</h3>
        <p>Yes. We service the full outdoor kitchen suite on the same visit — BBQ grill, outdoor refrigerator, outdoor wine cooler, side burners, and warming drawers. For Malibu, Bel Air, Newport Coast, Westlake Village, and Temecula properties with complete outdoor kitchens, scheduling everything on one visit is the efficient approach.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My Weber grill only gets to 250°F — is it broken?</h3>
        <p>Check the regulator first. Weber regulators enter a bypass safety mode when gas is released too quickly. Disconnect the tank, open all burner knobs for 30 seconds to bleed pressure, close them, and reconnect the tank slowly. This resets the regulator in about 40% of cases. If the problem persists, call us — gas valve or manifold issue.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

